00:15.400 --> 00:17.300
I love it when he plays the piano.

00:17.400 --> 00:19.200
No matter how gloomy it is outside,

00:19.500 --> 00:21.400
it makes everything seem
a little brighter.

00:21.700 --> 00:25.000
I feel the same way about bacon.

00:25.300 --> 00:27.300
DAPHNE:
You're so lucky to be musical.

00:27.600 --> 00:30.200
I'd give my right hand to be able
to play the piano the way you do.

00:30.500 --> 00:32.700
Hmm, sounds a bit like O. Henry
meets Stephen King.

00:32.900 --> 00:35.800
But still, if you're serious,
I'd be willing to give you lessons.

00:36.100 --> 00:37.300
I'd love that.

00:37.600 --> 00:39.300
I've wanted to play
ever since I was little,

00:39.600 --> 00:42.700
and my family would sing rugby songs
after my brothers' matches.

00:42.900 --> 00:45.700
I can still see them
all muddied and bloodied,

00:46.000 --> 00:48.000
belting out songs
like "The Old She-Crab"

00:48.300 --> 00:49.700
and "I Like a Moose."

00:51.000 --> 00:52.700
Once,
one of Michael's teeth fell out

00:53.000 --> 00:56.000
right in the middle
of "Four Old Whores."

00:57.100 --> 00:59.200
MARTIN: Hey, Fras,
how was your date last night?

00:59.400 --> 01:01.800
I'm having breakfast with you.
You do the math.

01:02.100 --> 01:04.200
- Ahem, coffee?
FRASIER: Please, thank you, Niles.

01:04.400 --> 01:06.200
Well, here's something
that'll cheer you up.

01:06.400 --> 01:09.100
Eight years ago today
I moved in with you.

01:09.400 --> 01:11.000
- Eight years? Ha, ha.
MARTIN: Ha, ha.

01:11.300 --> 01:13.300
- Are you sure?
- This is quite an anniversary.

01:13.600 --> 01:15.300
You weren't even with Lilith
for eight years.

01:15.600 --> 01:17.700
Please, Niles,
I hardly think it's the same thing.

01:17.900 --> 01:19.700
It's not that different.
If you were a woman,

01:19.900 --> 01:21.300
you'd be his common-law wife
by now.

01:21.600 --> 01:24.500
- Oh, well, now I don't think that's...
DAPHNE: And think about this.

01:24.700 --> 01:26.400
If that date had been
the perfect woman,

01:26.700 --> 01:29.700
you'd still have to be with her
nine years before you overtook him.

01:30.100 --> 01:32.400
Yes, and actually,
if you add the 18 years

01:32.700 --> 01:36.300
he spent at home prior to college,
well, they've been together 26 years.

01:37.100 --> 01:38.800
So we just missed
our silver anniversary?

01:39.000 --> 01:40.400
- All right.
- Yes, but good news,

01:40.700 --> 01:43.100
your 30th is pearl. Ha, ha.

01:43.400 --> 01:45.400
Well, I think
it's a remarkable accomplishment.

01:45.700 --> 01:48.200
Happy anniversary,
Dr. And Mr. Crane.

01:48.500 --> 01:50.200
NILES: Yes, here, here.
- Ha, ha.

01:50.500 --> 01:52.100
NILES:
Oh, here.

01:55.300 --> 01:57.400
I'm so sorry it didn't work out
with Lucy last night.

01:57.600 --> 02:01.300
But don't worry. I have tons
of other friends better than her.

02:02.000 --> 02:03.200
Well,

02:03.300 --> 02:06.500
thanks for starting at the bottom
and working your way up.

02:07.400 --> 02:08.699
- Hey, Roz. Dr. Crane.
FRASIER: Oh.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.400
- Hi, Daph. Hello, Dad.
- Oh, hey, Daphne.

02:11.700 --> 02:13.100
What, are you taking piano lessons?

02:13.300 --> 02:14.800
Yeah, Niles is gonna teach me.

02:14.900 --> 02:17.300
I'm so jealous.
I've always wanted to learn to play.

02:17.600 --> 02:19.800
- Well, why don't you sit in with us?
- Really?

02:20.100 --> 02:22.600
- Well, do you think Niles would mind?
- Of course not.

02:23.000 --> 02:25.700
And even if he does,
he's so polite you'll never know.

02:25.900 --> 02:28.400
Hi. I'd like to tell you
about our new frozen coffee drink,

02:28.600 --> 02:29.800
The Caffalanche.

02:30.100 --> 02:31.300
It comes in three flavours.

02:31.400 --> 02:35.000
Frosty Coffee, So Cocoa-Cold

02:35.400 --> 02:38.000
and Chilla-in-Vanilla.

02:38.200 --> 02:40.000
- I'll try the So Cocoa-Cold.
FRASIER: Ha, ha.

02:40.200 --> 02:41.600
Uh, black coffee, thanks.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.400
- I hate what's happened to coffee.
- Dad.

02:45.600 --> 02:47.300
Well, I'm just saying,
I'm a regular joe,

02:47.500 --> 02:49.900
- I like my joe regular.
- I like my joe regular. I know.

02:50.200 --> 02:52.400
What's wrong with plain, old coffee,
the way God made it?

02:52.700 --> 02:53.700
FRASIER:
Nothing.

02:54.000 --> 02:57.000
What is wrong, is subjecting me
to the same shopworn bellyaching

02:57.300 --> 02:58.600
every time you come in here.

02:58.900 --> 03:01.200
Well, excuse me for having an opinion
you don't agree with.

03:01.500 --> 03:03.700
I thought this was America.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.200
Oh, look, it is.

03:07.200 --> 03:09.700
I'm gonna get my coffee to go.

03:10.500 --> 03:12.400
That was a bit harsh, Dr. Crane.

03:12.700 --> 03:14.100
Eight years of the same complaints

03:14.300 --> 03:16.000
about the same things
in the same places.

03:16.300 --> 03:19.200
And I'll say, sometimes I think
he does it just to antagonize me.

03:19.500 --> 03:22.500
Just like an old married couple.

03:22.800 --> 03:23.900
It's cute, isn't it?

03:24.000 --> 03:25.400
Well, I got my black coffee.

03:25.700 --> 03:28.000
Of course, it was more expensive
than a whole meal used to be.

03:28.300 --> 03:31.600
Time was, you could get two eggs,
potatoes, choice of breakfast meat...

03:31.900 --> 03:34.600
And still get change back
from the nickel.

03:36.300 --> 03:37.600
Will you just take your coffee.

03:37.800 --> 03:39.700
See how he talks to me?

03:40.000 --> 03:42.900
- And on our anniversary too.
FRASIER: Oh.

03:46.100 --> 03:48.800
NILES: Now, I want you to position
your hands over the keyboard.

03:49.200 --> 03:52.500
Fingers relaxed, elbows loose.
Good.

03:52.800 --> 03:55.100
Okay, and shoulders low. Good, good.
How are we doing?

03:55.300 --> 03:57.600
- Fine.
- Okay, I guess.

03:57.900 --> 03:59.400
When do we get to press
on the keys?

03:59.600 --> 04:01.100
Whoa, whoa.

04:01.400 --> 04:02.500
We have a lot to learn first.

04:02.600 --> 04:04.600
It could be weeks
before we press down on the keys.

04:04.900 --> 04:06.300
I want to play a song.

04:06.500 --> 04:08.200
Yeah, isn't that why we're here?

04:08.400 --> 04:10.200
Well, all in due time. Here, wait.

04:10.300 --> 04:12.500
Just watch my hands
while I play a scale. Watch this.

04:12.700 --> 04:15.000
[PLAYING THE SCALE]

04:15.300 --> 04:16.700
FRASIER:
Pardon me, Niles,

04:16.899 --> 04:18.700
there was a programme
I planned on watching.

04:18.899 --> 04:21.399
Oh, of course. Uh, we'll continue
the lesson in Daphne's room.

04:21.700 --> 04:23.300
How can we learn without a piano?

04:23.500 --> 04:27.500
With these workbooks
and a box of adhesive stars.

04:32.400 --> 04:34.000
MAN [ON TV]:
<i>It would seem as though...</i>

04:34.100 --> 04:37.000
Brr, that guy sure looks cold.

04:37.300 --> 04:39.600
What are we watching?

04:40.400 --> 04:43.900
I'm watching <i>Lost on a Mountain.</i>

04:44.100 --> 04:45.200
Ah...

04:45.400 --> 04:47.400
<i>It is not remarkable that Everest...</i>

04:48.900 --> 04:50.200
That the mountain?

04:52.000 --> 04:53.800
Yes.

04:54.800 --> 04:56.900
Well, they sure don't look lost.

04:59.200 --> 05:00.700
That's the search party.

05:00.900 --> 05:02.400
Oh.

05:05.200 --> 05:06.400
So who's lost?

05:06.700 --> 05:08.500
Apparently you are.

05:08.800 --> 05:10.900
If you don't stop interrupting,
I will be too.

05:23.000 --> 05:24.700
- <i>nine climbers</i>
<i>from four different countries</i>

05:24.900 --> 05:26.700
<i>have come to the summit.</i>

05:26.900 --> 05:29.400
<i>They knew an approaching storm</i>
<i>might well hamper their efforts,</i>

05:29.700 --> 05:32.300
<i>but were determined</i>
<i>to press forward nonetheless.</i>

05:36.100 --> 05:37.600
[MUMBLES]
Pretzel?

05:41.100 --> 05:42.100
[CHAIR SCREECHES]

05:42.400 --> 05:44.800
- Do you mind?
- [MUMBLES] I'm sorry.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.500
- <i>but ascending Everest</i>
<i>is only half the journey.</i>

05:49.700 --> 05:51.900
<i>The journey</i>
<i>back down the mountain...</i>

05:53.900 --> 05:55.400
[CHAIR SCREECHES]

06:01.500 --> 06:02.600
[CHAIR SCREECHES]

06:05.100 --> 06:06.700
[CHAIR SCREECHES]

06:15.000 --> 06:18.500
<i>Still, he felt he had little choice</i>
<i>but to participate in the effort.</i>

06:18.800 --> 06:20.500
Oh, that's it, Dad!

06:20.700 --> 06:23.000
Is there nothing you do
that doesn't create some cacophony?

06:23.300 --> 06:25.800
Well, I didn't do it on purpose.
I was trying to be considerate.

06:26.100 --> 06:27.900
If you were,
you would have oiled that chair

06:28.100 --> 06:29.700
when it began squeaking
five years ago.

06:29.900 --> 06:32.800
Boy, I don't know what's got into you
but you've been a real jerk lately.

06:33.100 --> 06:34.500
You should watch TV
somewhere else.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.800
I should go elsewhere? I?

06:39.100 --> 06:40.100
Just what do you suggest?

06:40.400 --> 06:43.700
That I find, uh, a documentary bar
and watch it on their big screen?

06:45.000 --> 06:47.100
You know what?
I am just going to go take a talk.

06:47.300 --> 06:49.100
Leave you with the television.

06:49.400 --> 06:50.500
You enjoy yourself.

06:50.700 --> 06:53.000
Good day.

06:55.800 --> 06:56.900
[DOOR SLAMS]

06:58.200 --> 07:02.500
I wish you would stop
hanging your coat on my peg!

07:04.200 --> 07:06.200
NILES: Dad?
MARTIN: Down here.

07:06.400 --> 07:08.400
Oh, my God, Dad.

07:09.900 --> 07:11.000
Oh, I thought you'd capsized.

07:11.300 --> 07:13.800
No, I was oiling my chair.

07:14.100 --> 07:16.400
The squeaking was bugging Frasier.

07:16.700 --> 07:17.700
[NILES GASPS]

07:18.000 --> 07:20.200
The carpet is a whole shade lighter
under there.

07:20.500 --> 07:22.800
Oh. Except for those little black dots
you just made.

07:23.100 --> 07:24.200
Oh, shoot.

07:24.400 --> 07:25.800
- I better get a towel.
- I'll get it.

07:26.100 --> 07:28.100
No, it's all right. I'll get it. Oh!

07:28.800 --> 07:30.300
- Oh, my God.
- Ah! I'll get something

07:30.500 --> 07:32.400
to pick up the grease
and clean it up.

07:33.100 --> 07:35.200
MARTIN:
Oh, my God.

07:35.400 --> 07:36.500
What the hell's happened?

07:36.700 --> 07:38.600
Now, don't get upset.
I was oiling my chair,

07:38.900 --> 07:41.100
trying to get rid of the squeak,
and I had a little spill.

07:41.400 --> 07:43.500
Little spill?
I just had this carpet cleaned!

07:43.800 --> 07:47.100
- I'm sorry, it was an accident.
- Sure, Dad. It was an accident.

07:47.400 --> 07:49.000
It was an accident.
I saw him step on it.

07:49.300 --> 07:51.700
Niles, you know as well as I do,
there are no accidents.

07:52.000 --> 07:53.400
Just admit it, Dad.

07:53.500 --> 07:55.900
Your hostility toward me
has been building through the years,

07:56.300 --> 07:59.400
little by little, until you have
finally struck the Achilles' heel

07:59.700 --> 08:02.300
of my dÃ©cor, the Berber carpet.

08:03.300 --> 08:05.500
I did not do this on purpose.

08:05.700 --> 08:09.400
No? Then I suggest you dig deep
into the twisted caves

08:09.800 --> 08:10.900
of your subconscious,

08:11.100 --> 08:12.600
where malicious acts abide,

08:12.700 --> 08:15.300
clothed in the robes
of plausible excuses!

08:15.700 --> 08:17.700
[SHOUTS] For the last time,
this was not malicious!

08:18.000 --> 08:19.000
It was an accident!

08:19.100 --> 08:21.500
- I don't think you know the difference!
- Yes, I do!

08:21.800 --> 08:23.500
That was an accident!

08:23.700 --> 08:26.200
This is malicious!

08:33.500 --> 08:35.000
NILES:
What colour is the new carpet?

08:35.200 --> 08:39.799
I'm going up a shade
to harvest wheat.

08:40.200 --> 08:41.700
I thought the next shade up
was buff.

08:42.000 --> 08:45.700
It used to be but they've discovered
a whole new colour in between.

08:46.800 --> 08:49.900
So now it's tofu, putty, oatmeal,

08:50.200 --> 08:51.200
- almond,
- almond,

08:51.500 --> 08:53.100
- harvest wheat,
- harvest wheat,

08:53.300 --> 08:55.200
- and buff.
- Buff.

08:56.500 --> 08:58.300
That's going to be hard
to get used to.

08:58.500 --> 08:59.700
Hmm.

08:59.900 --> 09:01.000
Where's Daphne?

09:01.300 --> 09:02.800
Oh, she's out
taking a walk with Dad.

09:02.900 --> 09:05.000
An extra-long walk.

09:05.200 --> 09:06.900
Things have been a little tense
around here

09:07.200 --> 09:09.500
since the quote-unquote accident.

09:09.800 --> 09:10.700
It was an accident.

09:11.000 --> 09:12.200
Well, maybe.

09:12.700 --> 09:14.300
But don't you think the man
should work

09:14.500 --> 09:17.000
on some of his unresolved anger
toward me?

09:17.300 --> 09:19.300
NILES:
If you're asking me to choose sides,

09:19.600 --> 09:20.800
I'm not going to do it.

09:21.100 --> 09:25.400
The man just brings such hostility
into the room.

09:26.500 --> 09:27.500
[FRASIER SIGHS]

09:28.200 --> 09:29.600
Thank you.

09:29.700 --> 09:31.800
You know,
I've been thinking of, uh,

09:33.200 --> 09:34.700
sending him someplace.

09:35.400 --> 09:36.800
Like to a resort?

09:37.100 --> 09:38.800
Like to live with you.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
Oh, yes, the last resort.

09:43.200 --> 09:45.100
Making Dad move
does not solve your problem,

09:45.300 --> 09:46.300
it simply avoids it.

09:46.500 --> 09:49.100
Don't start preaching to me.
You've been avoiding him eight years.

09:49.400 --> 09:52.100
- I refuse to discuss this.
- And I refuse your refusal.

09:52.300 --> 09:53.400
Is something burning?

09:54.900 --> 09:56.500
- It smells like it.
- Are you cooking?

09:56.800 --> 09:58.900
And what is that supposed to mean?

10:00.100 --> 10:01.800
Oh, dear God, the chair!

10:02.100 --> 10:04.600
Oh, my God! Oh, here, Niles,
Niles, hand me this drop cloth here.

10:04.900 --> 10:07.200
- I'll smother it.
- All right, all right now, be careful.

10:07.400 --> 10:09.500
NILES: Quickly, quickly.
- Yeah, all right. Just...

10:09.800 --> 10:11.300
- Oh, look out below!
- Look out!

10:11.600 --> 10:13.200
- My God!
- Dr. Crane's moods

10:13.400 --> 10:17.400
never last long.
I'm sure we've seen the worst of it.

10:24.600 --> 10:26.800
- What do we do? What do we say?
- All right, calm down.

10:27.100 --> 10:28.800
The important thing is
it didn't hit anyone.

10:29.100 --> 10:31.000
At least we have that.
But how do we explain this?

10:31.200 --> 10:34.000
We just tell them what happened
as clearly and rationally as possible.

10:34.200 --> 10:35.900
Right, right. Rational.

10:36.500 --> 10:39.500
[SHOUTS] Oh, my God,
did you feel that earthquake?

10:39.900 --> 10:41.100
[SHOUTS]
What the hell happened?

10:41.300 --> 10:44.300
- Where's Daphne?
- She's down cleaning up the mess!

10:44.700 --> 10:46.200
Dad, I can explain.

10:46.400 --> 10:48.200
You threw my chair off the balcony?

10:48.500 --> 10:50.000
I'm so sorry. Just hear me out.

10:50.400 --> 10:51.700
- You crazy?
- I didn't mean to.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.400
Forget what it means to me,
you could've killed someone.

10:54.700 --> 10:58.800
- It was an accident!
- You said there are no accidents!

10:59.200 --> 11:00.200
Clearly I was wrong.

11:00.400 --> 11:02.200
I mean,
why on earth would I do such a thing?

11:02.500 --> 11:06.600
Because you've always been gunning
for that chair.

11:08.700 --> 11:10.800
I accidentally stain your carpet

11:11.100 --> 11:14.100
and you set fire to the one thing
in this apartment I care about

11:14.400 --> 11:17.000
and heave it out into the street!

11:18.000 --> 11:19.400
Dad, I am so sorry.

11:19.600 --> 11:20.600
I didn't mean to.

11:20.900 --> 11:21.900
Please, forgive me.

11:22.100 --> 11:24.500
- I'll buy you another chair.
- Ah, don't do me any favours.

11:24.700 --> 11:25.800
Please, Dad.

11:26.100 --> 11:28.000
I know you're angry right now
and that's normal.

11:28.200 --> 11:29.700
The healthiest thing you can do...

11:30.000 --> 11:31.800
Wanna know the healthiest thing
you can do?

11:32.400 --> 11:33.400
Shut my yap?

11:33.600 --> 11:34.700
Bingo!

11:40.500 --> 11:42.400
NILES:
Yes. Yes.

11:42.700 --> 11:44.600
Yes. No.

11:44.900 --> 11:46.200
I don't like this exercise.

11:46.400 --> 11:48.400
- It's too hard.
- No, no, no, you're doing fine.

11:48.700 --> 11:50.300
You just have to loosen up.
I'll show you.

11:51.300 --> 11:53.900
See?
It's just a little finger exercise.

11:54.300 --> 11:58.200
- I know another little finger exercise.
- Ha, ha.

11:58.500 --> 11:59.900
Daphne, you're not paying attention.

12:00.200 --> 12:01.500
Oh, yes, I am.

12:02.400 --> 12:04.900
Why don't we just cancel the lesson
and spend the day together?

12:05.200 --> 12:07.800
[STAMMERS] What kind of teacher
would I be if I did that?

12:08.100 --> 12:09.600
Oh, that's right.

12:09.900 --> 12:11.000
You're the teacher

12:11.300 --> 12:15.100
and I'm the naughty student
who wouldn't do her homework.

12:22.400 --> 12:23.800
[DOORBELL RINGS]

12:24.100 --> 12:27.100
Oh, that'll be Roz.

12:28.500 --> 12:29.600
[NILES SIGHS]

12:29.800 --> 12:31.500
Could you get that?

12:38.000 --> 12:39.200
DAPHNE: Hey, Roz.
- Hey, Daphne.

12:39.400 --> 12:42.600
- Hey, Roz. How'd it go this week?
ROZ: Niles.

12:44.100 --> 12:46.500
Okay, I guess.

12:47.800 --> 12:50.500
- But those exercises aren't easy.
- See?

12:50.800 --> 12:53.500
All right, look, if I'm going too fast,
we'll make some adjustments.

12:53.700 --> 12:56.600
I guess just do the best you can.

12:57.300 --> 12:58.600
[ROZ SIGHS]

12:58.800 --> 13:00.300
[ROZ CLEARS THROAT]

13:06.100 --> 13:08.100
- That's great!
- Ow.

13:08.400 --> 13:10.700
NILES: All right, do it again.
ROZ: Ahem.

13:16.300 --> 13:18.400
You see, Daphne, that's a song.

13:18.600 --> 13:20.800
You said we weren't going
to be playing songs.

13:21.100 --> 13:23.200
Wait, wait, now go down.

13:24.200 --> 13:26.400
Yes, good.

13:26.700 --> 13:29.600
Oh, my God, this is so cool.

13:30.000 --> 13:31.000
I want to play a song.

13:31.200 --> 13:32.400
NILES:
Well...

13:32.700 --> 13:35.000
And you will, Daphne,
as soon as you master your exercises.

13:35.300 --> 13:38.000
You know, why don't you try playing
along on your practise pad?

13:48.400 --> 13:50.300
Oh, shoot.

13:54.800 --> 13:57.000
Hello, Niles.

13:57.200 --> 13:59.400
Hey, Dad.
Um, taking Eddie for a walk?

13:59.600 --> 14:01.500
Yeah, I was afraid if I left him home,

14:01.800 --> 14:05.300
Frasier would set him on fire
and throw him off the balcony.

14:07.200 --> 14:08.600
You see what I'm putting up with?

14:08.900 --> 14:11.000
- Are you gonna let this go on forever?
- Me?

14:11.200 --> 14:13.300
He keeps insisting
I was lashing out deliberately,

14:13.600 --> 14:16.300
which I was not, although God knows
it would've been justified.

14:17.000 --> 14:18.600
What, because of the oil?

14:18.900 --> 14:22.500
This is a lot deeper and a lot darker
than oil and you know it.

14:22.900 --> 14:24.700
The man will not get off my back.

14:24.900 --> 14:27.300
Seems to me you've been giving
as good as you've been getting.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.500
Please.
Ever since our so-called anniversary,

14:29.700 --> 14:31.600
- he keeps insisting on...
NILES: Whoa, whoa,

14:31.800 --> 14:33.700
what does your anniversary
have to do with this?

14:36.200 --> 14:38.900
I guess it just set me off.

14:39.100 --> 14:42.200
It was as though everyone was saying
that the only significant relationship

14:42.600 --> 14:45.500
I'll ever have again is with my father.

14:45.800 --> 14:47.400
So you're not mad at Dad.

14:47.700 --> 14:49.800
You're just mad he isn't a woman.

14:51.900 --> 14:54.200
Well, I got my coffee. Nothing fancy.

14:54.500 --> 14:56.700
But if you don't like it,
you're welcome to set it on fire

14:57.000 --> 14:58.600
and throw it off the balcony.

14:58.900 --> 15:00.000
- Bye, Niles.
- No, wait, Dad.

15:00.800 --> 15:03.100
Frasier just said something
very interesting to me...

15:03.300 --> 15:04.700
- Niles.
- I think you should hear.

15:05.000 --> 15:06.900
- Niles.
- Please, let me help you through this.

15:07.200 --> 15:09.400
Don't forget, I've done my share
of couples counselling.

15:09.700 --> 15:11.700
[SHOUTS]
We are not a couple!

15:12.000 --> 15:16.600
I'm sorry, I only meant
that I am an experienced mediator.

15:17.000 --> 15:20.600
Now, Frasier,
tell Dad what you were just telling me.

15:23.500 --> 15:25.100
All right.

15:27.700 --> 15:29.500
I think...

15:30.300 --> 15:32.800
...that anniversary talk...

15:33.800 --> 15:35.300
...stirred up some issues for me.

15:36.800 --> 15:41.800
That our relationship
is the only one I'll ever have.

15:42.700 --> 15:45.200
That for all intents and purposes,

15:46.100 --> 15:49.000
you are my significant other.

15:51.400 --> 15:53.800
- And that's my fault?
- I didn't say it was your fault, Dad.

15:54.200 --> 15:57.100
You think it's a picnic living with you?
It's not exactly my dream either.

15:57.300 --> 16:00.100
Okay, no, wait, wait, wait, honesty.
This is good.

16:00.300 --> 16:02.300
I'm just saying
I've had a bit of a breakthrough.

16:02.600 --> 16:04.900
Dandy! You've had a breakthrough,
I've lost my chair.

16:05.200 --> 16:08.100
Maybe I could sit
on your breakthrough.

16:08.400 --> 16:10.000
I'll tell you what you can sit on!

16:10.200 --> 16:13.200
Okay, okay, okay. Wait, wait, wait,
let's just keep this constructive.

16:13.600 --> 16:14.900
If you're going to make progress,

16:15.000 --> 16:17.300
you're both going
to have to compromise.

16:17.600 --> 16:20.100
Now, which one of you is willing
to take the first step?

16:24.900 --> 16:26.500
Allow me.

16:33.600 --> 16:35.800
You do this for a living, do you?

16:36.500 --> 16:40.300
[SHOUTS] I do it
because I enjoy working with people!

16:43.600 --> 16:46.700
Niles, I've been thinking. Maybe you
and Roz should continue without me.

16:47.100 --> 16:49.000
- Why would we do that?
- Because she's good.

16:49.300 --> 16:51.400
- Just a second...
- No, no, no, don't worry about me.

16:51.700 --> 16:54.800
I'll find something easier to play,
like a stick.

16:57.100 --> 16:58.800
Daphne, I'm not gonna let you quit.

16:59.000 --> 17:00.400
You're just a slow starter.

17:00.500 --> 17:03.100
It may require a little more time
but you'll improve.

17:03.300 --> 17:06.099
- You really think so?
- You have to trust me.

17:06.500 --> 17:07.700
I don't care how long it takes.

17:07.900 --> 17:10.099
I am going
to make a pianist out of you.

17:10.400 --> 17:12.300
Thank you.

17:12.599 --> 17:15.300
You know, you're much nicer
than my old piano teacher.

17:18.099 --> 17:20.900
- You took lessons before?
- Hmm? Oh, yeah.

17:21.200 --> 17:23.500
Eight years of them.

17:26.200 --> 17:27.700
Mr. Cruikshank.

17:27.900 --> 17:30.000
You know, he once played
at the Royal Albert Hall.

17:30.300 --> 17:32.700
Oh, why did you stop
taking the lessons, honey?

17:33.000 --> 17:36.700
Well, it turns out Mr. Cruikshank
was an unstable man.

17:37.000 --> 17:39.900
He took his own life.

17:41.700 --> 17:44.900
Do you know I was the last person
to see him alive?

17:48.400 --> 17:50.600
Dad, Frasier's here.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.500
What's this?

17:55.700 --> 18:00.900
It's something I got to tell you
I'm sorry for being such a sorehead.

18:02.600 --> 18:04.500
Oh, Dad.

18:04.800 --> 18:05.800
I'm overwhelmed.

18:06.100 --> 18:07.800
Tied the bow myself.

18:07.900 --> 18:10.000
Just... Just pull on it.
It'll come right off.

18:10.200 --> 18:11.400
Yeah? All right.

18:18.600 --> 18:22.200
Oh, how... How unexpected.

18:22.500 --> 18:23.800
You don't like it.

18:24.100 --> 18:28.000
- No, no, I do. It, it's just that...
- I got some guy, Eduardo, to help me.

18:28.300 --> 18:30.100
I figured I couldn't miss.

18:30.800 --> 18:32.400
It's divine.

18:32.600 --> 18:34.800
That's what Eduardo said.

18:37.700 --> 18:40.700
There's just one problem.

18:41.000 --> 18:42.000
If you don't like it...

18:42.300 --> 18:45.400
I know, I can set it on fire
and throw it over the balcony.

18:46.200 --> 18:47.600
No,
I just meant you can take it back.

18:47.900 --> 18:49.000
I want you to be happy.

18:49.200 --> 18:51.300
Frasier, this is a wonderful gesture
on Dad's part.

18:51.400 --> 18:53.800
I do too, Niles. I do.
I'm... I'm very touched, Dad.

18:54.200 --> 18:56.100
Thank you. Thank you so much.

18:58.300 --> 19:02.300
It's just that I had something else
in mind. Uh...

19:02.600 --> 19:04.100
[DOORBELL RINGS]

19:04.700 --> 19:06.600
Well, I give up.
Try to do a nice thing...

19:06.900 --> 19:08.400
- What's the matter?
FRASIER: Just...

19:09.200 --> 19:11.000
Ah, good.
Gentlemen, come right in, please.

19:11.300 --> 19:14.900
Uh, just set it right over here.

19:15.200 --> 19:17.500
You bought a chair?
Thanks for telling me.

19:17.700 --> 19:20.000
Give me a chance.
I think you'll be pleasantly surprised.

19:20.400 --> 19:22.400
- I need somebody to sign for this.
- Yes, of course.

19:22.600 --> 19:24.700
In just a moment, please.
Could you wait at the door?

19:25.000 --> 19:26.200
Thank you.

19:26.500 --> 19:30.500
Everyone, I would like to introduce you
to the newest member

19:30.900 --> 19:33.900
of our furniture family.

19:38.200 --> 19:40.000
Where did you find this?

19:40.300 --> 19:42.700
You can't find that, Dad.
It doesn't exist anymore...

19:45.400 --> 19:47.500
...which is why I contacted
a master builder,

19:47.800 --> 19:50.300
showed him some photographs
and had him duplicate it.

19:50.600 --> 19:53.500
As for the material, I tracked down
the original manufacturer

19:53.700 --> 19:57.300
and once I got them to admit
they made it, I had them reweave it.

19:59.100 --> 20:01.500
- It must have cost a fortune.
FRASIER: Yes.

20:01.800 --> 20:04.700
Ironically, this is now
the most expensive piece of furniture

20:05.000 --> 20:06.900
in the entire apartment.

20:07.200 --> 20:10.000
Oh, it's beautiful! Thank you, son.

20:10.300 --> 20:12.900
Well done, Frasier.
Oh, it feels just the same.

20:13.300 --> 20:14.200
I don't want to get up.

20:14.400 --> 20:17.300
Well, that's a shame. I was planning
on taking us both out to dinner, Dad.

20:17.600 --> 20:19.300
- Anywhere you'd like.
- Even the steak house?

20:19.600 --> 20:22.100
Even the steak house.

20:22.400 --> 20:24.000
Niles, Daphne,
you're welcome to join us.

20:24.300 --> 20:26.100
Oh, sorry
but we're in the middle of my piano...

20:26.400 --> 20:28.100
We'd love to.

20:30.000 --> 20:34.100
You know, I'll bet we can get free pie
if we just tell them it's our anniversary.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.500
[MARTIN LAUGHS]

